Class LogStreamReader

    public abstract class LogStreamReader
extends java.lang.Thread
    Abstract class representing a source that reads and offers contents of a log (file or over ip).

    Thomas Obenaus

    • Method Detail

      • nextLine

        public java.lang.String nextLine()
                          throws LogStreamException
        Returns the next line that is available (was read from the log source). On accessing this method the line will be consumed, that means further calls to this method will result in different results (the next line).
        Returns:
        - the next line as String
        Throws:
        LogStreamException - - Thrown if no more lines are available. Please use hasNextLine() to check if more lines are available.

      • nextLines

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> nextLines()
                                           throws LogStreamException
        Returns the next lines that are available (was read from the log source). On accessing this method all lines will be consumed, that means further calls to this method will result in different results (the next lines).
        Returns:
        - the next lines as list of String's
        Throws:
        LogStreamException - - Thrown if no more lines are available. Please use hasNextLine() to check if more lines are available.

      • setStopOnReachingEOF

        public void setStopOnReachingEOF(boolean stopOnReachingEOF)
        Setting this flag to false the LogStreamReader continues reading even if the end of file was reached, assuming more lines will be added to the file soon (like tail -f ). Setting this flag to true the LogStreamReader will terminate immediately if the end of the file is reached.
        Parameters:
        stopOnReachingEOF -
